io.smudgr.engine.param

Class NumberParameter

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.smudgr.engine.param.Parameter
      • io.smudgr.engine.param.NumberParameter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Controllable, ProjectItem, ReflectableType

    public class NumberParameter
extends Parameter
    The NumberParameter class is a Parameter implementation for interacting with a numeric variable.

    A NumberParameter instance has a minimum value, a maximum value, and a step property for configuring the amount of change for the increment() and decrement() events.

      • setStep

        public void setStep(double s)
        Set the amount of change to occur on an increment or decrement event.

        Step must be greater than zero and less than or equal to maximum - minimum

        Provided value is clamped to that range, so negative values are set to 0 and values higher than maximum - minimum are set to maximum - minimum.

        Parameters:
        s - Amount of change
        See Also:
        increment(), decrement()

      • setReverse

        public void setReverse(boolean reverse)
        Set the reverse state of this NumberParameter.

        When this is set to true, increment() events will decrease the value, and decrement() events will increase the value.

        This is useful when it makes more sense for an increase event to decrease the actual value, and vice versa.

        Parameters:
        reverse - boolean
        See Also:
        setContinuous(boolean)

      • setContinuous

        public void setContinuous(boolean continuous)
        Set the continuous state of this NumberParameter.

        When this is set to true, increases in the value past the getMax() will cause the value to be set back to getMin(), instead of being clamped. The same is true if the value decreases past the getMin(), the value will be looped back to getMax()

        This is useful for when it makes sense for increment() and decrement() events to continue changing the value instead of hitting a ceiling or floor.

        Parameters:
        continuous - boolean
        See Also:
        setReverse(boolean)
